ft of Radoslav Sutnar","URL":"https://www.moma.org/collection/works/129068","ImageURL":"https://www.moma.org/media/W1siZiIsIjE3NTEzOCJdLFsicCIsImNvbnZlcnQiLCItcmVzaXplIDEwMjR4MTAyNFx1MDAzZSJdXQ.jpg?sha=0b844d4066099d08"},{"ObjectID":131032,"Title":"It's late and the wind carries a faint sound as it moves through the trees. It could be anything. The jingling of little bells perhaps, or the tiny flickering out of tiny lives. I stroll down the sidewalk and close my eyes and open them and wait for my, mind to go perfectly blank. Like a room no one has ever entered, a room without any doors or windows. A place where nothing happens.","Artist":"Ugo Rondinone","Date":"1999-2000","Medium":"Six-channel video (black and white and color, sound), aluminum, Plexiglas, neon","CreditLine":"Gift of Maja Hoffmann and of Franz Wassmer","URL":"https://www.moma.org/collection/works/131032","ImageURL":"https://www.moma.org/media/W1siZiIsIjE5NTUzNiJdLFsicCIsImNvbnZlcnQiLCItcmVzaXplIDEwMjR4MTAyNFx1MDAzZSJdXQ.jpg?sha=d8a61269ccca4a40"},{"ObjectID":132996,"Title":"Untitled #19","Artist":"José Antonio Suárez Londoño","Date":"1979–84","Medium":"Etching and aquatint","CreditLine":"Gift of the artist through the Latin American and Caribbean Fund","URL":"https://www.moma.org/collection/works/132996","ImageURL":"https://www.moma.org/media/W1siZiIsIjE5MTI4NCJdLFsicCIsImNvbnZlcnQiLCItcmVzaXplIDEwMjR4MTAyNFx1MDAzZSJdXQ.jpg?sha=598d3747e68eaadb"},{"ObjectID":133978,"Title":"Untitled from Favorite Objects","Artist":"Christian Boltanski","Date":"1998","Medium":"One from a portfolio of 264 color Xeroxes","CreditLine":"Gift of Lee and Ann Fensterstock, in honor of their daughters, Kate and Jane","URL":"https://www.moma.org/collection/works/133978","ImageURL":"https://www.moma.org/media/W1siZiIsIjE4MDUwMSJdLFsicCIsImNvbnZlcnQiLCItcmVzaXplIDEwMjR4MTAyNFx1MDAzZSJdXQ.jpg?sha=53f68fa51de5d9d8"},{"ObjectID":134960,"Title":"Untitled","Artist":"Francis Alÿs","Date":"","Medium":"Newspaper clipping","CreditLine":"